FUNCTIONS
---------

  func  InsertField (Dialog : PDialog;  Col,Row : integer;
		     Fmt : boolean;  ALabel,ATemplate : string)  : PView;

	Inserts a label and a DMX object into a Dialog window.
	This function makes it easier for the programmer to insert
	a tvDMX TInputFields object into a dialog window.

	  Parameters:
	    Dialog	--dialog into which this new view is inserted;
	    Col, Row	--starting column and row;
	    Fmt		--label/field orientation;
	    ALabel	--label string;
	    ATemplate	--tvDMX template string;

	  Returns:
	    PView	--pointer to the tvDMX display object.
		(Usually thrown away.  Compile with X+ compiler directive.)

	This idea can be translated to create similar functions for
	TInputLine objects, and others.  (See InsertText(), below.)


OBJECTS
-------


Object TDmxEditDlg
==================

    Object TDmxEditDlg is a TDmxEditor descendant designed for insertion
    into a dialog box.  This object can be found in unit StdDMX.

    This derivative has no special fields.


METHODS
-------

func  GetPalette  : PPalette;  VIRTUAL;
      Override: Often

      Returns a pointer to palette string suitable for dialog boxes.


proc  HandleEvent (var Event : TEvent);  VIRTUAL;
      Override: Never

      Calls TDmxEditor.HandleEvent() for all events except for kbTab,
      kbShiftTab or kbEsc keyboard events --which are handled by
      TDmxScroller.HandleEvent()-- to select other views.

Object TInputFields
===================

    Object TInputFields is a data editor designed to be used in the same
    manner as object TInputLine.  

    This derivative has no special fields.


METHODS
-------

constructor Init (InfoStr : string;  var Bounds : TRect);

      Calls TDmxEditor.Init() with a ^A code preceding InfoStr to make
      showzeroes TRUE for all fields.  No label or indicator fields are
      needed.  The data is allocated by InitData().
      GrowMode is set to gfGrowHiX.


func  DataSize  : word;  VIRTUAL;
      Override: Sometimes

      Returns the lower part of the longint DataBlockSize.
      See also: proc GetData() and SetData().


proc  DoneData;  VIRTUAL;
      Override: Often

      Pseudo-abstract method that can be overridden to process the data
      during the object's finalization.


proc  GetData (var Rec );  VIRTUAL;
      Override: Sometimes

      Copies DataSize() bytes from the view to Rec.


proc  HandleEvent (var Event : TEvent);  VIRTUAL;
      Override: Never

      Translates the following keyboard events:  kbUp, kbDown, kbPgUp and
      kbPgDn before calling TDmxEditDlg.HandleEvent().


proc  InitData (var AData );  VIRTUAL;
      Override: Sometimes

      Allocates enough data for the number of records that would fit in the
      window defined by Init().


proc  LoadData (var S : TStream);  VIRTUAL;
      Override: Sometimes

      Virtual method called by the Load() method.
      Reads the DataBlockSize field; allocates that amount for the pointer
      WorkingData; and reads the data into WorkingData^ from the stream.


proc  SetData (var Rec );  VIRTUAL;
      Override: Often

      Copies DataSize() bytes from Rec to the view.


proc  SetState (AState : word; Enable : boolean);  VIRTUAL;
      Override: Never

      Refer to TV Guide's TView.SetState() documentation.


proc  SetUpField;  VIRTUAL;
      Override: Never

      Called BEFORE each FIELD is edited.
      Calls TDmxEditor.SetUpField() and then adjusts a private field to
      react differently for dialog windows.


proc  StoreData (var S : TStream);  VIRTUAL;
      Override: Sometimes

      Virtual method called by the Store() method.
      Writes the DataBlockSize field and then writes the data from
      WorkingData^ to the stream.


